description: Number of different numbers that are formed by permuting digits of n.
links: A. Dunigan AtLee, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..100000.
formula: a(n) << n / (log_10 n)^4.5 by Stirling's approximation. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Sep 29 2011
prog: (Haskell)import Data.List (permutations, nub)a047726 n = length $ nub $ permutations $ show n-- _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jul 26 2011(PARI) a(n)=n=eval(Vec(Str(n)));(#n)!/prod(i=0,9,sum(j=1,#n,n[j]==i)!) \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Sep 29 2011
crossrefs: Cf. A055098. Identical to A043537 and A043562 for n<100.
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
